item.description:
This Is Bad You may often see C++ code like this
#include &lt;stdio.h&gt; #include &lt;math.h&gt; int main() { float x = sqrt(3.14); printf(&#34;%f&#34;, x); } These are C compatibility headers. Don&rsquo;t use them in C++.
Do This Instead Put the letter c in front, remove the .h and add the std namespace.
#include &lt;cstdio&gt; #include &lt;cmath&gt; int main() { float x = std::sqrt(3.14); std::printf(&#34;%f&#34;, x); }
